《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的丹尼尔·维克多（{{lang|en|Daniel Victor}}）认为“唐纳德·德朗普夫”是“有趣的标签”，但特朗普家族早在17世纪便已改姓，所以改姓之举与总统候选人没什么关系。维克多还指出，美国许多艺人和政治家都改过姓，如前总统[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]]与[[杰拉尔德·福特|杰拉尔德·福特]]，以及特朗普的对手[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]等。<ref name=NYT>{{cite news | title = Donald Drumpf: A Funny Label, but Is It Fair | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/03/us/politics/donald-drumpf-a-funny-label-but-is-it-fair.html | deadurl = no | first = Daniel | last = Victor | newspaper = [[纽约时报|The New York Times]] | issn = 0362-4331 | date = 2016-03-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190829003645/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/03/us/politics/donald-drumpf-a-funny-label-but-is-it-fair.html | archivedate = 2019-08-29 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 }}</ref>克里斯·马蒂什奇克（{{lang|en|Chris Matyszczyk}}）在{{lang|en|[[CNET|CNET]]}}发文批评节目“持续纠缠”特朗普，奥利弗的意图已经超出“讽刺”，而是着意要改变美国人的看法，促使他们不要投票支持特朗普<ref name="CNET">{{cite web | title = John Oliver slams Trump for 22 minutes, creates new hashtag for him | url = https://www.cnet.com/news/john-oliver-slams-trump-for-22-minutes-creates-new-hashtag-for-him/ | first = Chris | last = Matyszczyk | publisher = [[CNET|CNET]] | date = 2016-03-02 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190731173433/https://www.cnet.com/news/john-oliver-slams-trump-for-22-minutes-creates-new-hashtag-for-him/ | archivedate = 2019-07-31 }}</ref>。

[[麻省理工学院|麻省理工学院]]在节目播出后制出名为“深德朗普夫”（{{lang|en|DeepDrumpf}}）的推特机器人，利用[[神经网络|神经网络]]技术模仿特朗普发布推文<ref name=":0">{{Cite web | url = https://www.csail.mit.edu/news/postdoc-develops-twitterbot-uses-ai-sound-donald-trump | title = Postdoc develops Twitterbot that uses AI to sound like Donald Trump | last = Conner-Simons | first = Adam | date = 2016-03-03 | website = [[MIT計算機科學與人工智慧實驗室|MIT Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory]] | publisher = [[麻省理工学院|Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] | deadurl = no | access-date = 2020-09-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190918120422/https://www.csail.mit.edu/news/postdoc-develops-twitterbot-uses-ai-sound-donald-trump | archive-date = 2019-09-18 }}</ref>。据机器人创始人表示，“深德朗普夫”收集特朗普的推文片段，利用[[人工智能|人工智能]]学习语法结构，根据学到的特朗普语法风格输出推文<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.wired.co.uk/article/donald-drumpf-twitter-bot-ai | title = MIT's Trump AI uses neural networks to generate accurate nonsense | last = Rundle | first = Michael | date = 2016-03-04 | work = [[连线|Wired UK]] | access-date = 2020-09-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200310215407/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/donald-drumpf-twitter-bot-ai | archive-date = 2020-03-10 | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/kb7bez/this-donald-trump-twitter-bot-is-surprisingly-convincing-gop-republican-election-tweets | title = This Donald Trump Twitter Bot Is Surprisingly Convincing | last = Rogers | first = Kaleigh | date = 2016-03-04 | website = Motherboard | publisher = [[Vice传媒有限公司|Vice Media]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200401051125/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/kb7bez/this-donald-trump-twitter-bot-is-surprisingly-convincing-gop-republican-election-tweets | archive-date = 2020-04-01 | deadurl = no | access-date = 2020-09-09 }}</ref>。他还称，如果可用的数据更多，或是用上{{lang|en|Facebook}}人工智能系统能够分析的所有数据，神经网络就能更好地模仿特朗普<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{cite web | title = Drumpf Twitterbot learns to imitate Trump via deep-learning algorithm | url = https://www.cnet.com/news/drumpf-twitterbot-learns-to-imitate-trump-via-deep-learning-algorithm/ | first = Bonnie | last = Burton | publisher = [[CNET|CNET]] | date = 2016-03-04 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | quote = The Twitterbot DeepDrumpf takes its name from "Last Week Tonight" host and comedian John Oliver who lambasted Trump on his February 28 show | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200518234842/https://www.cnet.com/news/drumpf-twitterbot-learns-to-imitate-trump-via-deep-learning-algorithm/ | archivedate = 2020-05-18 }}</ref>。

《上周今夜秀》播出八天后，节目在{{lang|en|YouTube}}的累计观看次数已超1900万，是《上周今夜秀》最热门的分段视频<ref name="Explodes" />。相比之下，上一期节目主分段的八天播放量刚超过400万<ref>{{cite news | title = Forget 'Donald Drumpf.' This new John Oliver segment is well worth a few minutes of your time | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/03/07/forget-donald-trump-this-new-john-oliver-segment-is-well-worth-a-few-minutes-of-your-time/ | first = Aaron | last = Blake | newspaper = [[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]] | issn = 0190-8286 | date = 2016-03-07 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2018-07-31 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180731093525/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/03/07/forget-donald-trump-this-new-john-oliver-segment-is-well-worth-a-few-minutes-of-your-time/ }}</ref>。三月结束时，节目的{{lang|en|YouTube}}播放量达2330万次，{{lang|en|Facebook}}更达6200万次，两大社交媒体合计8500万次，创下{{lang|en|HBO}}节目的新纪录<ref>{{cite news | title = Even John Oliver enjoys a Drumpf bump | url = https://money.cnn.com/2016/03/30/media/john-oliver-donald-trump/index.html | first = Brian | last = Stelter | publisher = [[有线电视新闻网|CNN]] | date = 2016-03-30 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200519085431/https://money.cnn.com/2016/03/30/media/john-oliver-donald-trump/index.html | archivedate = 2020-05-19 }}</ref>。

截至3月8日，节目播出十天后，全部3.5万顶“让唐纳德变回德朗普夫”棒球帽均已通过{{lang|en|donaldjdrumpf.com}}网站售罄，{{lang|en|Google Chrome}}扩展程序也已下载43.3万次<ref name="Explodes" />。特朗普当选总统后不久，联合服装宣告破产，但这与生产上述棒球帽没有直接关系<ref name=":2" />。

自由职业记者罗森鲍姆（{{lang|en|S. I. Rosenbaum}}）在《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》发文，批评奥利弗以“唐纳德·德朗普夫”称呼总统候选人之举是蓄意嘲弄移民美国时将姓名[[盎格魯化|盎格魯化]]的民族团体，例如[[德裔美国人|德裔美国人]]。罗森鲍姆称，这个名字让人想到特朗普本人的[[仇外|仇外]]言论，都属于长期存在的文化趋势，“以听上去来自外国的姓名暗示此人不是纯正美国人。”<ref name="WaPost">{{cite news | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2016/03/03/john-olivers-donald-drumpf-jokes-play-on-the-same-ugly-xenophobia-trump-does/?tid=pm_opinions_pop_b | title = John Oliver's 'Donald Drumpf' jokes play on the same ugly xenophobia Trump does | last = Rosenbaum | first = S. I. | date = 2016-03-03 | newspaper = [[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]] | archivedate = 2018-07-31 | deadurl = no | issn = 0190-8286 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180731093704/https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2016/03/03/john-olivers-donald-drumpf-jokes-play-on-the-same-ugly-xenophobia-trump-does/?tid=pm_opinions_pop_b | accessdate = 2020-09-09 }}</ref>奥利弗本人后来表示笑话“有些失控”，再也没有在节目中提起<ref name="NME">{{cite news | last = Britton | first = Luke Morgan | title = John Oliver compares his 'Make Donald Drumpf Again' joke to Radiohead's 'Creep' | url = https://www.nme.com/news/tv/john-oliver-donald-drumpf-trump-radiohead-creep-1969532 | work = [[新音乐快递|New Musical Express]] | date = 2017-02-07 | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180731123345/https://www.nme.com/news/tv/john-oliver-donald-drumpf-trump-radiohead-creep-1969532 | archivedate = 2018-07-31 }}</ref>。他在接受《[[滾石_(雜誌)|滚石]]》杂志采访时称：“笑话对我们来说很快就会过时，一开始的确很不错，但就像[[湯姆·約克|湯姆·約克]]的歌曲《[[懦夫_(电台司令歌曲)|懦夫]]》（''{{lang|en|Creep}}''），现在我每次都跳过去不听”<ref name=":3">{{cite journal | last = Hiatt | first = Brian | title = John Oliver Takes on the Trump Era: The Rolling Stone Interview | periodical = [[滾石_(雜誌)|Rolling Stone]] | date = 2017-02-07 | archivedate = 2019-12-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20191225214911/https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-features/john-oliver-takes-on-the-trump-era-the-rolling-stone-interview-126096/ | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | url = https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-features/john-oliver-takes-on-the-trump-era-the-rolling-stone-interview-126096/ | journal =  }}</ref>。谈到节目是和[[第88屆奧斯卡金像獎|第88届奥斯卡颁奖典礼]]在同一晚播出时奥利弗表示，节目制作时并没有影响会特别大的感觉，但德朗普夫的称呼后来变得如此流行，“想来多少有点让人不舒服”<ref name=":3" />。

== 改姓时间争议 ==
[[File:U.S._Immigration_records_mentioning_Friedr_Trumpf_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]的16岁男子“弗雷德里·德朗普夫”，唐纳德·特朗普的爷爷[[弗雷德里克·特朗普|弗雷德里克·特朗普]]也是这年移民美国<ref name="newyorker20161001">{{Cite journal | url = http://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/an-immigrant-named-trump | title = An Immigrant Named Trump | last = Widmer | first = Ted | date = 2016-10-01 | periodical = [[紐約客|The New Yorker]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200709145323/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/an-immigrant-named-trump | archive-date = 2020-07-09 | deadurl = no | access-date = 2020-09-09 | journal =  }}</ref><ref name="wp20170803">{{Cite news | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/politics/wp/2017/08/03/under-trumps-new-immigration-rule-his-own-grandfather-likely-wouldnt-have-gotten-in/ | title = Under Trump's new immigration rule, his own grandfather likely wouldn't have gotten in | last = Bump | first = Philip | date = 2017-08-03 | newspaper = [[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]] | issn = 0190-8286 | access-date = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200610145911/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/politics/wp/2017/08/03/under-trumps-new-immigration-rule-his-own-grandfather-likely-wouldnt-have-gotten-in/ | archivedate = 2020-06-10 }}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite book | pages = 22–23 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=x2jUDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA23&lpg=PA23&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = Trump Revealed: The Definitive Biography of the 45th President | last = Kranish | first = Michael | last2 = Fisher | first2 = Marc | date = 2017-01-10 | publisher = Simon and Schuster | isbn = 9781501156526 | oclc = 965135878 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170924043635/https://books.google.com/books?id=x2jUDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA23&lpg=PA23#v=onepage&q&f=false | archivedate = 2017-09-24 | access-date = 2020-09-09 }}</ref>]]

媒体评论员都同意德朗普夫是特朗普祖先的姓氏，并且唐纳德·特朗普和父亲[[弗雷德·特朗普|弗雷德]]都从未以德朗普夫为姓<ref name="NYT" /><ref name="time201603" />{{refn|group="注"|该说法源自[[格温达·布莱尔|格温达·布莱尔]]（{{lang|en|Gwenda Blair}}）2015年再版的著作《[[特朗普家族：建立帝国的三代人|特朗普家族：建立帝国的三代人]]》（''{{lang|en|The Trumps: Three Generations That Built an Empire}}''），第26页。书中将德朗普夫姓氏追溯到1608年[[卡尔施塔特_(莱茵兰-普法尔茨州)|卡尔施塔特]]记载的汉斯·德朗普夫（{{lang|en|Hanns Drumpf}}）<ref name="time201603" />。}}，但在家族改姓的具体时间上无法达成一致，有认为是17世纪，也有认为是19世纪唐纳德的爷爷[[弗雷德里克·特朗普|弗雷德里克·特朗普]]移民美国之时<ref>{{cite web | title = ¿Quién es Donald J Drumpf y por qué genera tanta controversia en EE.UU.? | url = https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias/2016/03/160303_eeuu_elecciones_quien_es_donald_drumpf_bd | publisher = BBC Mundo | accessdate = 2020-09-09 | archivedate = 2018-07-31 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180731220048/https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias/2016/03/160303_eeuu_elecciones_quien_es_donald_drumpf_bd }}</ref>。据[[迈克尔·克拉尼什|迈克尔·克拉尼什]]（{{lang|en|Michael Kranish}}）和[[马克·费希尔|马克·费希尔]]（{{lang|en|Marc Fisher}}）2017年的著作《[[揭密特朗普|揭密特朗普]]》（''{{lang|en|Trump Revealed}}''）记载，“特朗普”姓氏的确立时间尚无定论；唐纳德爷爷出生的德国村庄卡尔施塔特立有特朗普家族墓碑，上面列出的姓氏很多，“如德龙布（{{lang|en|Dromb}}）、德伦布（{{lang|en|Drumb}}）、德朗普夫（{{lang|en|Drumpf}}）、特伦（{{lang|en|Trum}}）、特龙布（{{lang|en|Tromb}}）、特龙普（{{lang|en|Tromp}}），以及特伦普夫（{{lang|en|Trumpf}}和{{lang|en|Trumpff}}）”<ref name=":1" />。

部分评论员认为，弗雷德里克·特朗普原名“弗雷德里希·德朗普夫”（{{lang|en|Friedrich Drumpf}}），是他将姓氏改成特朗普<ref name="wipreview" /><ref name="dw20150909" />。格温达·布莱尔（{{lang|en|Gwenda Blair}}）曾长期为唐纳德立传，她在2015年接受[[德国之声|德国之声]]采访时称，唐纳德的“爷爷弗雷德里希·德朗普夫于1885年来到美国”，当年他16岁，跟随大批德国人一起移民美国<ref name="dw20150909">{{cite web | title = What Donald Trump learned from his German grandpa Friedrich Drumpf | website = [[德国之声|Deutsche Welle]] | date = 2015-09-09 | url = https://www.dw.com/en/what-donald-trump-learned-from-his-german-grandpa-friedrich-drumpf/a-18701551 | access-date = 2020-09-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200801021328/https://www.dw.com/en/what-donald-trump-learned-from-his-german-grandpa-friedrich-drumpf/a-18701551 | archivedate = 2020-08-01 }}</ref>。家谱网站{{lang|en|[[Ancestry.com|Ancestry.com]]}}（“祖先.{{lang|en|com}}”）公布包括特朗普和[[阿斯特家族|阿斯特家族]]在内众多名门望族的谱系后，《[[紐約每日新聞|紐約每日新聞]]》于2015年9月初发文，称弗雷德里克·德朗普1869年在德国出生时原名“弗雷德里希·德朗普夫”<ref>{{Cite news | url = http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/trump-astor-weathy-nyc-families-wills-revealed-article-1.2345156 | title = Trump, Astor and other wealthy NYC families' wills revealed | last = Adams Otis | first = Ginger | date = 2015-09-02 | newspaper = [[紐約每日新聞|New York Daily News]] | access-date = 2020-09-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200520034706/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/trump-astor-weathy-nyc-families-wills-revealed-article-1.2345156 | archive-date = 2020-05-20 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。1885年美国移民纪录记有来自卡尔施塔特的“{{lang|en|Friedr. Trumpf}}”（“弗雷德里·德朗普夫”），弗雷德里克便是这年进入美国<ref name="newyorker20161001" /><ref name="wp20170803" /><ref name=":1" />。

部分媒体认为特朗普家族是在17世纪改姓。布莱尔2015年再版的著作《特朗普家族：建立帝国的三代人》声称，特朗普家族是在[[三十年戰爭|三十年戰爭]]期间改姓，17世纪就有家族先辈取名“约翰·菲利普·特朗普”（{{lang|en|John Philip Trump}}）。布莱尔还称，弗雷德里克·特朗普原名弗雷德里希·特朗普，他的父亲叫约翰内斯·特朗普（{{lang|en|Johannes Trump}}），生于19世纪。<ref name="BlairBook">{{cite book | title = The Trumps: Three Generations of Builders and a Presidential Candidate | archivedate = 2016-03-05 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=uJifCgAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y | first = Gwenda | last = Blair | publisher = [[西蒙與舒斯特|Simon and Schuster]] | pages = 26–27 | date = 2001 | accessdate = 2020-09-10 | isbn = 9781501139369 | oclc = 944246546 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305090641/https://books.google.com/books?id=uJifCgAAQBAJ }}</ref>《[[波士頓環球報|波士頓環球報]]》和丹尼尔·维克多抱持同等立场<ref name="TBG" />，维克多称“虽有不少误解，但特朗普先生与关系最近的亲属都和改姓无关。奥利弗先生所言‘某位很有远见的先祖’也很谨慎”<ref name="NYT" />。《[[衛報|衛報]]》的凯特·康诺利（{{lang|en|Kate Connolly}}）走访卡尔施塔特后撰文表示，弗雷德里克本名“弗雷德里希·特朗普”，镇上的教区登记册记有前后五百年的特朗普家族人士姓名，其中根本没有“德朗普夫”<ref>{{cite news | title = Kallstadt, Germany: on the trail of 'the Donald' in the Trump ancestral home | url = https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jan/29/kallstadt-germany-on-the-trail-of-the-donald-in-the-trump-ancestral-home | first = Kate | last = Connolly | newspaper = [[衛報|The Guardian]] | date = 2016-01-29 | accessdate = 2020-09-10 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2020-09-06 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200906015542/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jan/29/kallstadt-germany-on-the-trail-of-the-donald-in-the-trump-ancestral-home }}</ref>。

多份来源声称，弗雷德里希、其父其姑都姓特朗普，所以改姓时间应该是在18世纪前。家谱组织{{lang|en|[[FamilySearch|FamilySearch]]}}称弗雷德里希·特朗普的父亲叫约翰·伊·特朗普（{{lang|de|Johann Ii Trump}}）<ref>{{cite encyclopedia | type = database | title = Friedrich Trump | url = https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:NCR1-KF8 | publisher = Deutschland Geburten und Taufen | via = [[FamilySearch|FamilySearch]] | accessdate = 2016-04-07 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160407214603/https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:NCR1-KF8 | archivedate = 2016-04-07 }}</ref>。[[Dotdash|阿邦网]]旗下的{{lang|en|About.com}}网站刊登系谱家的研究结果，称唐纳德·特朗普的爷爷叫弗雷德里希·特朗普，太公叫克里斯蒂安·约翰内斯·特朗普（{{lang|de|Christian Johannes Trump}}）<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.thoughtco.com/ancestry-of-donald-trump-1421916 | title = Ancestry of Donald Trump – Great Grandparents | last = Powell | first = Kimberly | date = 2017-03-03 | website = [[Dotdash|Thoughtco.com]] | publisher = [[IAC_(公司)|IAC]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200731211652/https://www.thoughtco.com/ancestry-of-donald-trump-1421916 | archivedate = 2020-07-31 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2020-09-10 }}</ref>。约书亚·肯德尔（{{lang|en|Joshua Kendall}}）2013年的著作《美国强迫症：建立国家的强迫能量》（{{lang|en|''America's Obsessives: The Compulsive Energy That Built a Nation''}}）称，弗雷德里克的父亲和姑姑，即唐纳德的太公和太姑婆分别叫约翰·特朗普（{{lang|en|John Trump}}）和夏洛特·路易丝·特朗普（{{lang|en|Charlotte Luise Trump}}）<ref>{{cite book | title = America's Obsessives: The Compulsive Energy That Built a Nation | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=uQaety2SvzQC&pg=PT26&lpg=PT26&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false | first = Joshua | last = Kendall | publisher = Grand Central Publishing | via = [[Google圖書|Google Books]] | year = 2013 | accessdate = 2020-09-10 | quote = John Henry Heinz's mother was Charlotte Luise Trump, a sister of the Donald's great-grandfather, John Trump. | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160429213920/https://books.google.com/books?id=uQaety2SvzQC&pg=PT26&lpg=PT26#v=onepage&q&f=false | archivedate 